@startuml tailgate_control_to_tgm_position_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title Tailgate Control To TGM Position Signal Flow\n(power-tailgate control request -> TGM position/power publication)

participant "Tailgate control source\nassist / open request / actuator" as Ctrl #F4F7FB
participant "Vehicle state\nDriveState" as Veh #E8F0FE
participant "TGM\ntailgate owner" as TGM #FFF4CC
participant "Body observers" as Obs #FCE8FF

== Tailgate Control Inputs ==

Ctrl -> TGM : frmPowerTailgateCtrlStateMsg\nTailgateAssistMode / OpenRequestState / TailgateActuatorCmd
Veh -> TGM : frmVehicleStateCanMsg\nDriveState
activate TGM
TGM -> TGM : normalize stale control / vehicle inputs
TGM -> TGM : derive TailgateOpenState from\nOpenRequestState and actuator command
TGM -> TGM : derive TailgatePowerState / TailgatePosition
note right of TGM
Representative outputs
- TailgateOpenState
- TailgatePowerState
- TailgatePosition
end note

== Tailgate Publish ==

TGM -> Obs : frmTailgateStateMsg
TGM -> Obs : traceable tailgate position/power state
deactivate TGM

note over Ctrl, Obs
Representative runtime chain
1. Tailgate control request enters TGM
2. TGM applies drive-state and control gating
3. TGM derives power/open/position state
4. Observers confirm the resulting tailgate movement state
end note

@enduml
